text: I'm fairly certain there's not enough words in my vocabulary to describe how I feel about this, however, I'll do my best.  There are so many messages being sent out in this amazing hour.  Thanks for sharing this with your YouTube admirers!  The solidarity that flows from this group is beautiful!  The language is joyful and tearful at the same time.  The many, many smiles were stunning.   The talents and artistry flowed flawlessly from everyone involved and carried me away to another place at times.  From the happiness of the children, to the depth of sorrow on violence, my emotions were overwhelming at times...which means you did an outstanding performance as always!  I'm not sure how I've missed this for a whole year...but timing is everything and this morning was a perfect time for me to find it.  Have a blessed day!

text:
I would add, likely an Art exposure, this shading continuous in the light, melting instrumental sounds with light, cityscapes, it is something, might be said, that goes straight to something else, from the antropocene to the lithoscene ... music for the vibration of the polis. Ta

Parentesi - √à stra bello questo disco, strumentalmente lo adoro ... cerco la versione se c'√®, se no, please! Quando potete! Vorrei sentirle tutte cmq, non ho paura... per√≤ si, sto cercando il cosiddetto diamante grezzo con dentro la sua storia e a me sembra che questo disco abbia potenzialit√† non del tutto espresse, sbaglio? Ho visto un video clip da Zeno e mi sa che ho visto Johnny nel concerto di uno dei partecipanti : che occhio da falco! Cos√¨ lo abbiamo cercato e la citt√† √® perfettamente emblematica, solo che qui la citt√† √® concreta, squadrata, virtuale negli spazi, nelle ombre, nei rumori, come la luce √® antropica nell'attesa. Il film diventa subito una metafora del cerchio della vita, come un quadro simbolista. Appena lo osservi un po' ci vediamo le pennellate di luce e ombra intrecciate con i suoni in un modo cos√¨ denso da apparire come un'opera che trasborda dal Neorealismo al Postmodern. Il violino ... qualcosa che suona direttamente dentro di se come la voce.
C'√® sempre qualcosa che sfiora il vestimentario, dagli abiti di Johnny, Will e Chris smorzati da Guy... che si tiene il suo giubbotto come se non avesse trovato la misura e poi i ninnoli alla batteria: Will riesce a creare il senso del sipario e la vista da sopra, il senso di un'utopia attesa, solare, come nel racconto di Tommaso Campanella.

text: I am sorry to say that I think Cold Play is losing the plot! Nice views of Jordon but all the jigging around doesn't show that they are maturing into timeless musicians - this is very disappointing! The way forward is to bring orchestral arrangements into their music with other influences of jazz and blues that we see in one of the songs - if you take a look at Simply Red in Cuba, you will see what I mean. Also, I suggest that Chris Martin's singing is letting the side down and doesn't reflect his creativity that he obviously has.  Cold Play, if you read my words please move on from all this jumping about and enlarge your circle of musicians that can give a depth of sound and originality that I see that you are now looking for! Disappointing! I was hoping for something better!
